arge\"><a href=\"https://www.dropbox.com/s/s84tmzwn6mh6w2x/WordPress-Google-Sitemap-Generator--sitemap-in-robots-txt.png?raw=1\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\"><img src=\"https://www.dropbox.com/s/s84tmzwn6mh6w2x/WordPress-Google-Sitemap-Generator--sitemap-in-robots-txt.png?raw=1\" alt=\"\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Current text:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>❗️ Your site is currently blocking search engines! Visit the <a href=\"#\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Reading Settings</a> to change this.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>☑︎ Add sitemap URL to the virtual robots.txt file.<br /><sup>This links the sitemap in the robots.txt generated by WordPress. A real robots.txt file must NOT exist in the site directory!</sup></p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Proposed textual changes:</strong> (feel free to take portions you deem useful)</p>\n\n\n\n<p>ℹ️ Our plugin setting <em>☑︎ Add sitemap URL to the virtual robots.txt</em> is independent from WordPress <a href=\"#\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Reading Settings</a> currently set to the opposite, namely: <em>☑︎ Discourage search engines from indexing this site</em>. <strong>Rest assured</strong>: For now this does not make a difference. But as soon as you disable our plugin, the WordPress setting takes precedence.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>[  Hide  ]    ☐ and don&#8217;t show this again</p>\n\n\n\n<p>☑︎ Add sitemap URL to the virtual robots.txt file.<br /><sup>A real robots.txt file must NOT exist in the site directory! If ON sitemap gets linked in the virtual robots.txt generated by WordPress and suppresses whatever is set in WordPress <a href=\"#\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Reading Settings</a>.</sup></p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n<ul id=\"bbp-topic-revision-log-16729796\" class=\"bbp-topic-revision-log\">\n\n	<li id=\"bbp-topic-revision-log-16729796-item-16729799\" class=\"bbp-topic-revision-log-item\">\n		This topic was modified 1 month, 2 weeks ago by <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/users/abitofmind/\" title=\"View abitofmind&#039;s profile\" class=\"bbp-author-link\"><span  class=\"bb