ere&#8217;s what I&#8217;ve tried:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Changing the sitemap name and re-submitting</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Unchecking the &#8216;discourage search engines from indexing&#8217; checkbox in Settings in WordPress</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Adding a / and removing a / before the sitemap name</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Excluding the sitemap from caching in the plugin</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Unchecking the &#8216;block indexing in the virtual Robots-X file&#8217;</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Waiting a week</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>If I test the live URL inside Google Search Console it shows that Google can fetch and crawl the sitemap – but even if I uncheck the &#8216;block indexing&#8217; checkbox inside XML-Sitemaps the result still finds a &#8216;noindex&#8217; tag. Not sure if that is an issue.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>My site was infected with malware so all my Google results are showing Spam links. The issue is fixed so they don&#8217;t redirect to a spam website, but I still am very anxious for GSC to read my sitemap as the Google result SEO titles are still spam.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Please let me know what else I can try.</p>\n						\n					\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"josh1u1are\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:25;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:67:\"\n					\n					\n					\n					\n					\n\n					\n					\n\n					\n					\n					\n				\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:85:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/cannot-read-properties-of-null-reading-classlist/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:193:\"&lt;span class=&quot;